Function neutral_analytical::nseSpeciesAbundanceCumulativeDistribution¶

  • Defined in File neutral_analytical.cpp

Function Documentation¶

std::map<unsigned long, long double> neutral_analytical::nseSpeciesAbundanceCumulativeDistribution(const unsigned long &community_size, const long double &speciation_rate)¶

Get the species abundances probability distribution for a set of community parameters within a non-spatial neutral model of ecology.

The abundances will be cumulative probabilities.

Return
Parameters
  • community_size: the number of individuals in the community
  • speciation_rate: the speciation rate
